# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1891-baltimore-orioles-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1891-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1891-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1891-baltimore-orioles-season/1891-baltimore-orioles-season] In their last season in the American Association, the **1891 Baltimore Orioles** finished in fourth place (third among teams that played a full schedule) with a record of 71–64.
[src:1891-baltimore-orioles-season/1891-baltimore-orioles-season] After the season, the AA folded, and the Orioles joined the National League.
